                <title xml:id="name971-4" xml:lang="en" source="#bib971-1" syriaca-tags="#syriaca-headword">Sharbel (text)</title>
                <author xml:lang="fr" source="#bib971-1" ref="http://syriaca.org/person/42">
                    <persName xml:lang="en-x-gedsh" syriaca-tags="#syriaca-headword">
                        <forename sort="1">Yaʿqub</forename>
                        <addName type="untagged-title" sort="2">of Serugh</addName>
                    </persName> — <persName xml:lang="syr" syriaca-tags="#syriaca-headword">
                        <forename sort="1">ܝܥܩܘܒ</forename>
                        <addName type="untagged-title" sort="2">ܕܣܪܘܓ</addName>
                    </persName> (<persName xml:lang="fr">
                        <forename>Jacques</forename>
                        <addName type="untagged-title">de Serugh</addName>
                    </persName>)</author>
                <note xml:lang="syr" type="incipit" source="#bib971-1">
                    <quote>ܫܪܒܝܠ ܟܘܡܪܐ ܕܗܘܐ ܣܗܕܐ ܒܚܪܬ ܝܘ̈ܡܘܗܝ ܬܒܥܢܝ ܡܐܡܪܐ ܗܒ ܠܝ ܡܪܢ ܕܥܠܘܗܝ ܐܡܪ.</quote>
                </note>
                <note xml:lang="fr" type="incipit" source="#bib971-1">
                    <quote>Le prêtre des idoles Sharbêl qui devint martyr à la fin de ses jours m’a demandé un discours; donne-moi, Seigneur, de parler de lui.</quote>
                </note>
                <note xml:lang="syr" type="explicit" source="#bib971-1">
                    <quote>ܒܕܡܐ ܡܟܝܪܐ ܘܕܡܐ ܫܩܠܬ ܘܕܡܐ ܝܗܒܬ ܒܪܝܟ ܕܒܚܘܒܗ ܠܕܡܐ ܕܣܗ̈ܕܐ ܚܠܛ ܥܡ ܕܝܠܗ.</quote>
                </note>
                <note xml:lang="fr" type="explicit" source="#bib971-1">
                    <quote>Fiancée par le sang elle a reçu et donné le sang; béni soit celui qui dans son amour mêle le sang des maryrs au sien.</quote>
                </note>
                <note type="editions">
                    <bibl source="#bib971-1" xml:id="bib971-4">
                        <author>Mösinger, G.</author>
                        <title>Monumenta Syriaca ex Romanis codicibus collecta II</title>
                        <citedRange>Oeniponti, 1878, p. 52-63</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                </note>
                <note xml:lang="en" type="MSS" source="#bib971-1">
                    <bibl xml:id="bib971-5">ms Vatican, Borgia Syr. 128, f. 170v-175v</bibl>
                </note>
                <note xml:lang="en" type="MSS" source="#bib971-1">
                    <bibl xml:id="bib971-6">ms Oxford, Bodleian Library, syr. 135 (Poc. 404), f. 324-327</bibl>
                </note>
